<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Inward1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Inward,</orth> adj. 1) internal, interior: <cit><quote>an i. bruise,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 58</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>i. sickness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these i. wars,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 107</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the i. man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 6</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 2, 57</bibl>. <emph>his i. soul</emph> == his inmost soul, the depth of his soul: <bibl n="shak. luc 1779" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1779</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. luc 1779" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1779</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.227" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 227</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 11</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.148" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 148</bibl>.<lb />2) seated in the mind: <cit><quote>that i. beauty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 434" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 434</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>i. ill,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 91" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>i. vice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 91" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 91</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>in i. worth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 16.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 16, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.46.14" default="NO" valid="yes">46, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 39</bibl>. II Chor. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 39</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13</bibl>
<lb />3) not known to many, confidential, private: <cit><quote>if either of you know any i. impediment why you should not be conjoined,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what is i. between us, let it pass,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 102</bibl></cit>.
<lb />4) privy to one's thoughts, familiar: <cit><quote>who is most i. with the royal duke?</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.8" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 4, 8</bibl></cit>.

